  "summaries": [
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":1,"summary":"Moses recounts God's command to leave Horeb, the appointment of judges, the sending of spies, and Israel's fearful rebellion at Kadesh-barnea."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":2,"summary":"Moses reviews the journey through the wilderness, passing Edom, Moab, and Ammon, and the defeat of King Sihon of Heshbon."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":3,"summary":"Moses recounts the defeat of King Og of Bashan, the division of the trans-Jordan land, and God's refusal to let Moses cross the Jordan."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":4,"summary":"Moses exhorts Israel to obey God's statutes, warns against idolatry, designates cities of refuge, and testifies of God's uniqueness."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":5,"summary":"Moses restates the Ten Commandments given at Horeb and recounts the people's fear at hearing God's voice from the fire."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":6,"summary":"Moses delivers the Shema—the command to love God with all heart, soul, and might—and instructs parents to teach God's words diligently."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":7,"summary":"God commands Israel to destroy the Canaanite nations and their idols, affirming Israel's election as a treasured people."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":8,"summary":"Moses warns Israel not to forget God in prosperity, reminding them of the manna and wilderness discipline."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":9,"summary":"Moses recounts Israel's repeated rebellions, including the golden calf, to show that God's favor is not due to their righteousness."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":10,"summary":"God renews the stone tablets, sets apart the Levites, and calls Israel to circumcise their hearts and love the stranger."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":11,"summary":"Moses sets before Israel blessings for obedience and curses for disobedience, commanding them to teach their children."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":12,"summary":"Instructions to worship only at the place God chooses, destroying all Canaanite worship sites and altars."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":13,"summary":"Warnings against false prophets and any who entice to idolatry, with strict penalties to purge evil from Israel."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":14,"summary":"Laws distinguishing clean and unclean animals, and instructions for tithing produce and livestock."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":15,"summary":"Laws for the release of debts every seventh year, generosity toward the poor, and the release of Hebrew servants."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":16,"summary":"Instructions for observing Passover, the Feast of Weeks, and the Feast of Tabernacles, and the appointment of judges."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":17,"summary":"Laws for judicial cases, the punishment of idolaters, and regulations for a future king who must study the law."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":18,"summary":"Provisions for the Levitical priests, prohibition of occult practices, and the prophecy of a great Prophet like Moses."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":19,"summary":"Laws establishing cities of refuge for the innocent manslayer, boundary protection, and the requirement of multiple witnesses."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":20,"summary":"Laws of warfare, including exemptions from battle, terms of peace, and the treatment of besieged cities."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":21,"summary":"Laws for unsolved murders, captive women, firstborn inheritance rights, and the punishment of a rebellious son."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":22,"summary":"Laws on lost property, gender distinction in clothing, building safety, and various regulations on sexual morality."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":23,"summary":"Laws about exclusion from the assembly, camp purity, escaped slaves, prohibition of cult prostitution, vows, and gleaning."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":24,"summary":"Laws on divorce, pledges, kidnapping, leprosy, just wages for laborers, and gleaning for the poor."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":25,"summary":"Laws on judicial punishment limits, levirate marriage, honest weights and measures, and the command to remember Amalek."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":26,"summary":"The firstfruits offering ceremony and tithing declaration, culminating in God's affirmation of Israel as his treasured people."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":27,"summary":"Moses commands the writing of the law on stones at Ebal, building an altar, and the pronouncement of twelve curses."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":28,"summary":"Extensive blessings promised for obedience and devastating curses threatened for disobedience, including exile and suffering."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":29,"summary":"Moses renews the covenant in Moab, warning that secret things belong to God but revealed things demand obedience."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":30,"summary":"Promise of restoration after repentance and the climactic call to choose life, love God, and cleave unto him."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":31,"summary":"Moses commissions Joshua, writes the law, commands its periodic reading, and foretells Israel's future apostasy."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":32,"summary":"The Song of Moses: a prophetic poem contrasting God's faithfulness and perfection with Israel's corruption and ingratitude."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":33,"summary":"Moses pronounces individual blessings upon each tribe of Israel, praising God as Israel's eternal refuge and protector."},
    {"book":"Deuteronomy","chapter":34,"summary":"Moses views the promised land from Nebo, dies, and is buried by God; Joshua assumes leadership, and Moses is eulogized."}
  ],
